Sometimes boys are more
resilient than men.

1:20:46.542 --> 1:20:48.042
How did you survive?

1:20:51.981 --> 1:20:53.247
I didn't get sick.

1:20:55.718 --> 1:20:57.218
I was the carrier.

1:21:02.058 --> 1:21:04.658
(sniffs)

1:21:04.660 --> 1:21:07.294
Arthur:
<i> We were in, uh,</i>
<i> close quarters.</i>

1:21:09.632 --> 1:21:11.465
Unsanitary conditions.

1:21:13.603 --> 1:21:17.104
When we came back infected,
we didn't know.

1:21:19.408 --> 1:21:20.908
<i> We were weapons.</i>

1:21:24.046 --> 1:21:25.512
I killed them.

1:21:27.817 --> 1:21:29.149
No.

1:21:29.151 --> 1:21:31.285
Millions of people died,
Mr. Lambden.

1:21:33.656 --> 1:21:35.656
But what about
those eight boys?

1:21:36.492 --> 1:21:38.192
At the bottom of the lake.

1:21:39.662 --> 1:21:41.161
What about them?

1:21:42.899 --> 1:21:45.432
That ain't your fault, either.

1:21:45.434 --> 1:21:46.901
I keep on surviving.

1:21:51.307 --> 1:21:53.274
(sniffing)

1:21:53.276 --> 1:21:54.742
You saved us.

1:22:05.388 --> 1:22:11.191
(watch ticking)

1:22:14.964 --> 1:22:20.968
(inspiring instrumental)

1:22:20.970 --> 1:22:24.038
¶

1:22:36.619 --> 1:22:37.918
Hey.

1:22:39.121 --> 1:22:40.621
Let's go home.

1:22:41.958 --> 1:22:48.028
(inspiring instrumental)

1:22:48.030 --> 1:22:51.098
¶

1:22:59.742 --> 1:23:06.146
(music swells)

1:23:06.148 --> 1:23:09.216
¶

1:23:26.502 --> 1:23:27.768
Hello, young man.

1:23:28.704 --> 1:23:30.304
Having a good time?

1:23:30.306 --> 1:23:36.110
(soaring dramatic music)

1:23:36.112 --> 1:23:38.178
¶

1:23:49.959 --> 1:23:51.625
Canon Rutherford:
<i> I'll see if they</i>
<i> made it there.</i>

1:23:51.627 --> 1:23:54.028
You take the other motor
to the Rosedale docks.

1:23:55.097 --> 1:23:56.096
If you hadn't come-

1:23:56.098 --> 1:23:57.264
Come now.

1:23:57.266 --> 1:23:58.532
Let's make a move.

1:23:58.768 --> 1:24:00.034
Boy:
<i> Mr. Manley!</i>

1:24:04.874 --> 1:24:10.878
(gentle instrumental)

1:24:10.880 --> 1:24:12.946
¶

1:24:27.897 --> 1:24:33.834
(lively instrumental)

1:24:33.836 --> 1:24:35.903
¶

1:24:56.492 --> 1:24:57.791
Robert:
<i> Mr. Lambden.</i>

1:24:59.662 --> 1:25:03.397
<i> Do you remember in the</i>
<i> Somme, the Basilica?</i>

1:25:06.902 --> 1:25:07.968
<i> On top of the spire,</i>

1:25:07.970 --> 1:25:09.870
<i> there was a tremendous statue.</i>

1:25:11.540 --> 1:25:13.540
<i> It had been damaged</i>
<i> by the shelling.</i>

1:25:14.643 --> 1:25:16.844
<i> It hung there at</i>
<i> a 45 degree angle.</i>

1:25:18.447 --> 1:25:20.180
<i> People said if it</i>
<i> fell from the spire,</i>

1:25:20.182 --> 1:25:21.682
<i> the Germans would win.</i>

1:25:23.319 --> 1:25:25.953
<i> But some French engineers</i>
<i> decided to fix fate.</i>

1:25:26.856 --> 1:25:30.057
<i> They installed a cable,</i>
<i> so it would remain secure.</i>

1:25:31.193 --> 1:25:32.860
<i> So it would not fall.</i>

1:25:32.862 --> 1:25:34.461
(melancholy instrumental)

1:25:34.463 --> 1:25:38.265
(boys cheering and shouting)

1:25:39.869 --> 1:25:41.568
Arthur:
<i> Are you telling me</i>

1:25:42.071 --> 1:25:44.471
<i> I'm the statue,</i>

1:25:44.473 --> 1:25:46.974
<i> dangling from the spire?</i>

1:25:46.976 --> 1:25:48.242
Robert:
<i> No, Arthur.</i>

1:25:49.645 --> 1:25:51.111
<i> You're the cable.</i>

1:25:58.587 --> 1:26:00.020
Canon Rutherford:
<i> Chief Coroner is here.</i>

1:26:00.022 --> 1:26:01.188
The police are here.

1:26:01.190 --> 1:26:02.489
The, uh-

1:26:03.025 --> 1:26:05.926
firemen have brought
grappling hooks.

1:26:09.131 --> 1:26:10.597
Where are the boys?

1:26:10.599 --> 1:26:11.865
Canon Rutherford:
<i> They're outside.</i>

1:26:13.969 --> 1:26:15.469
They want to see you.

1:26:28.684 --> 1:26:31.919
<i> A greater love hath</i>
<i> no man than this.</i>

1:26:33.756 --> 1:26:35.989
<i> (muffled prayer)</i>

1:26:45.434 --> 1:26:46.700
Arthur:
<i> Hello, boys.</i>

1:26:48.270 --> 1:26:49.670
<i> Our number one priority</i>

1:26:49.672 --> 1:26:53.106
is to get you back
to your families.

1:26:53.108 --> 1:26:55.442
Waller, Leonard and Will,

1:26:55.444 --> 1:26:57.377
<i> go to the hospital.</i>

1:26:57.379 --> 1:26:58.645
We're not leaving you.

1:27:00.249 --> 1:27:01.815
We're staying right here.

1:27:10.626 --> 1:27:14.361
Waller, gather a team
and dismantle the tents.

1:27:14.363 --> 1:27:15.596
Understood.

1:27:15.598 --> 1:27:16.997
Arthur:
<i> Leonard,</i>

1:27:16.999 --> 1:27:19.933
<i> gather some boys and</i>
<i> empty the cookhouse.</i>

1:27:19.935 --> 1:27:21.235
Right away.

1:27:22.871 --> 1:27:24.137
Will.

1:27:29.612 --> 1:27:31.812
Will,

1:27:31.814 --> 1:27:35.415
if you could take down
the flag, that'd be swell.

1:27:35.417 --> 1:27:36.717
Yes, sir.

1:27:36.719 --> 1:27:38.385
Mr. Manley, if you
could help him?

1:27:39.221 --> 1:27:40.687
Of course, Mr. Waller.

1:27:41.490 --> 1:27:42.789
<i> Well let's get to work.</i>

1:27:44.426 --> 1:27:50.230
(pensive instrumental)

1:27:50.232 --> 1:27:54.301
¶

1:28:17.693 --> 1:28:24.298
(music swells)

1:28:24.300 --> 1:28:28.368
¶
